It’s been an overly busy week (thankfully all good things, things I have prayer and wanted for YEARS) but when I look down at my to-do list, it feels like nothing got done. 

My time is something I really value, now more than ever since becoming a mom - and I just had a week where I felt like I didn’t get much done for work.  I had a lot of anxiety about it because I felt so behind but I decided to wake up today with a different mindset and follow through with my morning routine (lmk if you guys would want to see a short video on my morning routine). 

The result? My most productive day of the week so far and I feel AMAZING! A small shift in your mindset has the ability to change your entire day, week, month... life! And following through with your morning routine, not rushing the start of your day and giving some time to YOU also has so much power to set the right tone for your day. 

I wanted to share this mini video for anyone who this may help, even in the slightest! You are doing amazing💖

Life update. We moved!!!!! Wow. It doesn’t feel real!

Late Mother’s Day post incoming lol because mom lifeeeee 

I can’t believe I get to be a mom to my two babies, Mia and Dev who have shown me what love truly means. As cliche as it sounds, being a mom means watching your heart live outside your body. The best, yet the hardest job in the world. My kids have taught me (and continue to) teach me so much about myself and seeing them grow and develop is my life’s greatest gift. 

And to my own mom who I need now more than ever. I’m so grateful. All the sacrifices she made as a single parent means the world to me. Best Nani in the world to my kids too. 

To all the moms out there, you are doing great!!!! Your children are so lucky to have you, happy Mother’s Day!
